tational name from one or more of several places so named, such as Walford (Herefordshire), Walford in Leintwardine (also Herefordshire), Walford in Baschurch (Shropshire), and possibly Walford Hall in Hampton in Arden (Warwickshire), though this last may be a manorial placename deriving from the surname. The Herefordshire placenames probably derive from Old English <i>walh</i> ‘foreigner, Welshman’ (genitive plural <i>wala</i>) + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’. The Shropshire placename derives from Old English <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’ + <i>ford</i>. If it does not derive from the surname, the Warwickshire placename probably has the same etymology as the Herefordshire placenames.","perhaps occasionally a habitational name from Walford in Wimborne Minster (Dorset). The placename probably derives from Old English <i>walt</i> ‘unsteady’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Walford was born in 1441, in Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Walford. He married Margaret Krahenbuhl on 4 October 1505, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, and was buried in Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1441–":"1441–Surnud","1441–Male":"1441–Surnud","1485–1547":"1485–1547","1515–1565":"1515–1565","1547":"1547","1565":"1565","1441":"1441","1485":"1485","4 October 1505":"4. oktoober 1505","1515":"1515","Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Myddle, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walford, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1441–":"1441–Kuollut","1441–Male":"1441–Kuollut","1485–1547":"1485–1547","1515–1565":"1515–1565","1547":"1547","1565":"1565","1441":"1441","1485":"1485","4 October 1505":"4. lokakuuta 1505","1515":"1515","Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Myddle, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walford, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1441–":"1441–Décédé","1441–Male":"1441–Décédé","1485–1547":"1485–1547","1515–1565":"1515–1565","1547":"1547","1565":"1565","1441":"1441","1485":"1485","4 October 1505":"4 octobre 1505","1515":"1515","Myddle, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Myddle, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walford, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Walford est né en 1441, à Walford, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de William Walford. Il a épousé Margaret Krahenbuhl le 4 octobre 1505, à Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé à Myddle, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, et a été enterré à M